{'input': {'source_code': '@SuppressWarnings("unchecked")\npublic static Map<String, String> deserializeOffsetMap(String lastSourceOffset) throws IOException {\n  Map<String, String> offsetMap;\n  if (lastSourceOffset == null || lastSourceOffset.isEmpty()) {    \n    offsetMap = new HashMap<>();  \n  } else {\n    offsetMap = JSON_MAPPER.readValue(lastSourceOffset, Map.class);  \n  }\n  return offsetMap;\n}\n', 'repo_info': {'repo': 'streamsets/datacollector', 'path': 'stagesupport/src/main/java/com/.../OffsetUtil.java', 'function_name': 'OffsetUtil.deserializeOffsetMap'}}, 'output': 'The provided code is a static method named `deserializeOffsetMap` in the `OffsetUtil` class located in the `stagesupport/src/main/java/com/...` directory of the `streamsets/datacollector` repository.\n\nHere\'s a breakdown of the code:\n\n```java\n@SuppressWarnings("unchecked")\npublic static Map<String, String> deserializeOffsetMap(String lastSourceOffset) throws IOException {\n  Map<String, String> offsetMap;\n  if (lastSourceOffset == null || lastSourceOffset.isEmpty()) {\n    offsetMap = new HashMap<>();\n  } else {\n    offsetMap = JSON_MAPPER.readValue(lastSourceOffset, Map.class);\n  }\n  return offsetMap;\n}\n```\n\n1. The method is declared as `public static`, indicating that it can be called without creating an instance of the class.\n\n2. The method takes a single parameter `lastSourceOffset` of type `String`, which represents the serialized offset data.\n\n3. The method returns a `Map<String, String>`, which is a map with string keys and string values.\n\n4. The `@SuppressWarnings("unchecked")` annotation is used to suppress a specific unchecked warning related to the use of `Map.class` with the `JSON_MAPPER.readValue` method. It assumes that the deserialization will result in a `Map<String, String>`.\n\n5. Inside the method, a variable `offsetMap` of type `Map<String, String>` is declared.\n\n6. The method checks if `lastSourceOffset` is `null` or an empty string using the condition `if (lastSourceOffset == null || lastSourceOffset.isEmpty())`.\n\n7. If `lastSourceOffset` is `null` or an empty string, a new `HashMap<String, String>` is created and assigned to `offsetMap`.\n\n8. If `lastSourceOffset` is not `null` or an empty string, the method uses the `JSON_MAPPER` (presumably an instance of `com.fasterxml.jackson.databind.ObjectMapper`) to deserialize the JSON string into a `Map<String, String>` using the `readValue` method. The `Map.class` parameter specifies the type of the deserialized object.\n\n9. Finally, the method returns the `offsetMap`.\n\nIn summary, this method deserializes a JSON string representing offsets into a `Map<String, String>` if the `lastSourceOffset` is not `null` or an empty string. If the `lastSourceOffset` is `null` or an empty string, it returns an empty `HashMap<String, String>`.', 'metric': 0.21409335727109513}